00:44:44.120 --> 00:44:45.220
GABE ZICHERMANN: Yeah, yeah.

00:44:45.220 --> 00:44:47.940
Why not?

00:44:47.940 --> 00:44:49.190
So here's the thing.

00:44:54.220 --> 00:44:56.750
I've tried to of express this
probably a couple different

00:44:56.750 --> 00:44:57.220
ways today.

00:44:57.220 --> 00:44:59.390
So I just want to go back
to it for a second.

00:44:59.390 --> 00:45:02.800
I don't really think that
there's any situation in which

00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:05.360
we shouldn't be thinking
about how to gamify it.

00:45:05.360 --> 00:45:10.430
Because every single idea,
concept, product, business in

00:45:10.430 --> 00:45:14.750
the world lives or dies by
its consumer engagement.

00:45:14.750 --> 00:45:16.150
Everything.

00:45:16.150 --> 00:45:19.900
I tend to describe it as
a last mile problem.

00:45:19.900 --> 00:45:22.557
It is the last mile problem of
every idea, especially in

00:45:22.557 --> 00:45:23.400
technology.

00:45:23.400 --> 00:45:26.510
You've got a great concept, an
amazing product, just like the

00:45:26.510 --> 00:45:29.100
other 5 million people here in
the valley coming up with

00:45:29.100 --> 00:45:31.700
their great ideas, launching
their problem products.

00:45:31.700 --> 00:45:33.940
And where do they all
end up failing?

00:45:33.940 --> 00:45:35.920
They all end up feeling because
they're not able to

00:45:35.920 --> 00:45:38.500
get user adoption.

00:45:38.500 --> 00:45:40.250
That's where we have
the last mile part.

00:45:40.250 --> 00:45:42.250
It's not we don't have great
ideas, because we have lots of

00:45:42.250 --> 00:45:43.260
great ideas.

00:45:43.260 --> 00:45:45.400
It's that we don't have methods
for actually getting

00:45:45.400 --> 00:45:46.940
people to do that thing.

00:45:46.940 --> 00:45:49.620
And no matter how good our ideas
are, if people don't do

00:45:49.620 --> 00:45:53.580
that thing, then our idea
isn't worth squat.

00:45:53.580 --> 00:45:58.060
It turns out that engagement
behavior change, itself, is

00:45:58.060 --> 00:46:01.140
actually, I think, the currency
on which companies

00:46:01.140 --> 00:46:02.910
are priced.

00:46:02.910 --> 00:46:06.480
So the more businesses are able
to change behavior and

00:46:06.480 --> 00:46:10.020
the more you in your own career
are able to touch your

00:46:10.020 --> 00:46:12.360
examples of behavior change,
the more people

00:46:12.360 --> 00:46:14.220
will pay for you.

00:46:14.220 --> 00:46:15.980
That's what they're
paying for.

00:46:15.980 --> 00:46:18.360
You can call it traffic.

00:46:18.360 --> 00:46:22.130
But the discussion is shifting
from traffic to engagement.

00:46:22.130 --> 00:46:24.930
And that's the currency of our--
the coin of the realm,

00:46:24.930 --> 00:46:26.530
if you will.

00:46:26.530 --> 00:46:28.860
So gamify everything.

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:31.430
And probably, you won't
have a choice, p.s.

00:46:31.430 --> 00:46:32.680
That's the other piece of it.

00:46:35.140 --> 00:46:39.330
This next consumer isn't going
to care unless the experience

00:46:39.330 --> 00:46:40.990
has feedback, friends,
and fun.

00:46:40.990 --> 00:46:42.020
They're just not
going to care.

